title: Passing array of `return` to a function with wrong number/type of arguments causes an ICE

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: regression-from-stable-to-beta
labels.description: Performance or correctness regression from stable to beta.

body:
Found this one while researching for #98894, probably has a related cause (since #92364 diagnostics call `check_expr` a second time which confuses the compiler). This is an ICE though so opening a dedicated issue. cc @compiler-errors ### Code ```Rust (|_, ()| ())([return, ()]); ``` ### Bisection searched nightlies: from nightly-2022-04-10 to nightly-2022-05-09 regressed nightly: nightly-2022-04-17 searched commit range: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/compare/3f391b84552f210adec7893b50c5da74f9362ae4...878c7833f6c1ff10e2fd89074e5bd4ef5ff15936 regressed commit: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/07bb916d44a66d2caba427c7ee132bbeb245977b
bisected with cargo-bisect-rustc v0.6.3 Host triple: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu Reproduce with: ```bash cargo bisect-rustc --regress=ice --end=2022-05-09 ``` `src/main.rs`: ```rust fn main() { (|_, ()| ())([return, ()]); } ```
### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.64.0-nightly (20a6f3a8a 2022-06-25) binary: rustc commit-hash: 20a6f3a8a8ce5ae18d06b12cd7904bc5294ca753 commit-date: 2022-06-25 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.64.0-nightly LLVM version: 14.0.5 ``` ### Error output ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'assertion failed: `(left == right)` left: `WarnedAlways`, right: `Maybe`', compiler/rustc_typeck/src/check/expr.rs:1309:13 ```
